01:09.710 --> 01:12.779
Would you like
somethin' to drink?

01:12.781 --> 01:15.817
Danny: What?

01:15.819 --> 01:21.558
When I come back, I could
bring you somethin' to drink.

01:21.560 --> 01:22.859
A Coke.

01:22.861 --> 01:24.762
Ice?

01:24.764 --> 01:27.999
Sure.

01:29.936 --> 01:35.802
[ Music ]

01:56.635 --> 01:58.605
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

02:02.171 --> 02:04.339
Janet: I don't know why you
wouldn't ride with us.

02:04.341 --> 02:07.076
Amantha: Something seemed karmically
wrong about that, mother.

02:07.078 --> 02:08.943
Well, we're late, karma or not.

02:08.946 --> 02:11.247
So, have your ID ready and
take off all your jewelry.

02:11.249 --> 02:13.283
I've been there a lot
more than you lately.

02:13.285 --> 02:15.152
I know the drill.

02:15.154 --> 02:17.221
Ted, Jr's calling in.

02:17.223 --> 02:18.322
Ha, what?

02:18.324 --> 02:21.225
Does he wanna stop at
7-11 for a ding dong?

02:21.227 --> 02:24.062
We'll see you there, Amantha.

02:24.064 --> 02:25.363
Hey.

02:25.365 --> 02:26.331
Ted Jr.: Hey, mama.

02:26.333 --> 02:27.499
Tell dad he better pick it up.

02:27.501 --> 02:29.534
It's gonna suck if we're
late for this thing.

02:29.536 --> 02:31.970
Ted, Teddy says pick it up.

02:31.972 --> 02:33.538
Um, Teddy?

02:33.540 --> 02:34.540
Yeah, mama?

02:34.542 --> 02:36.275
Could you call me Janet?

02:36.277 --> 02:37.276
What?

02:37.278 --> 02:39.645
Just for a while, just until
Daniel gets used to all

02:39.647 --> 02:41.848
the changes and everything.

02:45.486 --> 02:49.657
She wants us to call
her Janet for a while.

02:49.659 --> 02:52.994
Tawney: I can't imagine what
she's going through, right now.

02:52.996 --> 02:54.929
Don't assume it's all good.

02:54.931 --> 02:56.664
What do you mean?

02:56.666 --> 02:59.000
Sheriff still believes
he was in on it.

02:59.002 --> 03:00.068
A lot of people do.

03:00.070 --> 03:01.970
Well, you don't think that, do
you, that he could've done

03:01.972 --> 03:03.571
somethin' that horrible to her?

03:03.573 --> 03:05.373
Well, I sure did.

03:05.375 --> 03:07.442
I mean, he was convicted.

03:07.444 --> 03:10.378
What would a rational person
think all these years?

03:10.380 --> 03:11.976
Now, hell, I don't know.

03:11.978 --> 03:14.341
I never even met the guy.

03:14.343 --> 03:16.175
I still don't understand.

03:16.177 --> 03:17.109
Come on, Tawney.

03:17.111 --> 03:18.176
What was I supposed to do?

03:18.178 --> 03:20.878
Go down to death row
and introduce myself?

03:20.880 --> 03:23.748
"Hi, I'm Ted-- I'm, uh,
your new stepbrother, and

03:23.750 --> 03:26.050
I'm gonna be takin' over the
business you thought would be

03:26.052 --> 03:28.418
yours one day."

03:28.420 --> 03:31.921
I mean, why torture the guy?

03:31.923 --> 03:36.759
I hate to say it, but we all thought
he'd be dead by now anyway.

03:39.563 --> 03:48.303
[ Music ]

03:49.338 --> 03:51.906
[ Cell phone ringing ]

03:51.908 --> 03:53.674
Jon: Hey, Amantha.

03:53.676 --> 03:54.876
Where are you?

03:54.878 --> 03:56.144
Closer by the day.

03:56.146 --> 03:58.379
Uh, if you don't get here
soon, I may have to recruit

03:58.381 --> 04:00.648
some people from the crowd
to play the family.

04:00.650 --> 04:02.984
At least pick people who
are glad he's still alive.

04:02.986 --> 04:04.219
I'll take a poll.

04:04.221 --> 04:06.187
Have you seen him yet?

04:06.189 --> 04:07.655
No, not yet.

04:07.657 --> 04:08.890
But, he got the suit?

04:08.892 --> 04:10.425
I was assured he did.

04:10.427 --> 04:12.527
God, I hope I don't fall apart.

04:12.529 --> 04:14.796
It's okay if you do.

04:21.536 --> 04:23.770
Are you kidding me?

04:23.772 --> 04:25.806
What?

04:25.808 --> 04:26.840
What, Jon?

04:26.842 --> 04:28.943
Roland Foulkes just showed up.

04:28.945 --> 04:31.178
Roland Foulkes: How ya
doin' today-- Joel.

04:31.180 --> 04:32.479
Son of a bitch.

04:32.481 --> 04:33.847
So nice to see you.

04:33.849 --> 04:35.149
Hi, how are you?

04:35.151 --> 04:36.717
I'll have a comment after.

04:36.719 --> 04:38.485
So nice to see you, again.

04:43.725 --> 04:46.794
They say it's pretty
crazy out there.

04:46.796 --> 04:48.863
Where's your tie?

04:48.865 --> 04:53.101
Uh, I couldn't remember.

04:53.103 --> 04:54.335
Remember?

04:54.337 --> 04:57.405
How to tie it.

04:57.407 --> 05:01.342
It's, uh, a Windsor knot.
I think.

05:01.344 --> 05:03.878
Hey, man, I could
tie it for you.

05:03.880 --> 05:06.748
I mean, I don't know if it's a
Windsor, but it's the kind

05:06.750 --> 05:08.850
I do on me, for church.

05:08.852 --> 05:09.717
Tie it on me.

05:09.719 --> 05:12.654
Then, we transfer it to you.

05:13.422 --> 05:17.391
Almost two decades ago, I
prosecuted a case where

05:17.393 --> 05:22.696
Miss Hannah Abigail Dean was
brutally raped and murdered.

05:22.698 --> 05:26.200
DNA testing on material sitting
in some box in an evidence room

05:26.202 --> 05:31.005
all these years is not gonna change
that fact or bring that girl back.

05:31.007 --> 05:35.843
We must remember that she was
only 16 years old, a mere child,

05:35.845 --> 05:40.816
with her whole life ahead of
her, and that life was taken

05:40.818 --> 05:46.822
in the most heinous manner I
personally have ever seen.

05:46.824 --> 05:49.258
Female reporter: Sources are
reporting that Mr. Holden is

05:49.260 --> 05:52.427
still considered a suspect,
in spite of the DNA results.

05:52.429 --> 05:56.732
Well, I'm sure our current DA
will address some of these complex

05:56.734 --> 06:00.502
procedural questions this new breed
of lawyer loves to go on about.

06:00.504 --> 06:04.640
I'm just here to remind ya'll
of a few things that seem

06:04.642 --> 06:07.809
to have gotten lost
in this DNA hysteria.

06:07.811 --> 06:11.713
Daniel Holden confessed
to raping Hannah.

06:11.715 --> 06:15.016
He confessed to killing Hannah.

06:15.018 --> 06:19.421
Now, where I come from, we put a lot
of stock in that sort of thing.

06:19.423 --> 06:25.594
And please-please, don't-don't
report that he was exonerated.

06:25.596 --> 06:29.131
The sentence was vacated on
a technicality, which sure

06:29.133 --> 06:32.601
as hell does not make
him an innocent man.

06:34.337 --> 06:42.477
I don't know who picked out your tie,
but... they sure have style.

06:46.248 --> 06:48.917
- There was nothing to--
- Technicality my ass.

06:48.919 --> 06:50.318
It wasn't his sperm.

06:50.320 --> 06:52.220
Senator is just doing
what he does best.

06:52.222 --> 06:53.154
Stay on message.

06:53.156 --> 06:53.921
Keep it simple.

06:53.923 --> 06:54.856
Repeat, repeat, repeat.

06:54.858 --> 06:56.524
Ever heard of forced
confession, asshole?

06:56.526 --> 06:57.392
Amantha, please?

06:57.394 --> 06:59.127
I should just walk over there
and kill him, right now.

06:59.129 --> 07:00.896
They can take me
straight to death row.

07:00.898 --> 07:01.596
Skip the middle man.

07:01.598 --> 07:03.799
Just remember, everything we do
is being watched and judged.

07:03.801 --> 07:05.501
Can I at least
flip him the bird?

07:05.503 --> 07:06.401
No.

07:06.403 --> 07:08.737
Everyone can say their
hellos to Daniel, briefly.

07:08.739 --> 07:11.110
And then, we have to go straight
to the press conference.

07:11.112 --> 07:13.049
Hellos and
introductions, you mean?

07:13.051 --> 07:15.385
I don't know why these
two are even here.

07:15.387 --> 07:16.386
Ahem.

07:16.388 --> 07:17.821
More family looks better.

07:17.823 --> 07:19.590
Remember, just because he's
getting out doesn't mean

07:19.592 --> 07:21.058
this thing is over yet.

07:21.060 --> 07:22.893
At least look like
you give two shits.

07:22.895 --> 07:24.829
Amantha, please.

07:37.143 --> 07:43.132
[ Music ]

07:50.490 --> 07:52.224
That suit fits you perfect.

07:52.226 --> 07:54.860
Goddamn-- I mean, perfect.

07:54.862 --> 07:56.062
You are perfect, brother.

07:56.064 --> 07:59.332
You are so damn perfect.

08:08.143 --> 08:10.377
Hello, Daniel.

08:12.547 --> 08:14.414
Hello, mother.

08:14.416 --> 08:16.083
Oh!

08:16.085 --> 08:17.751
Oh!

08:17.753 --> 08:19.720
Oh, God!

08:21.490 --> 08:24.792
[ Sobbing ]

08:30.265 --> 08:32.533
My sweetheart.

08:43.078 --> 08:45.513
We are not here to
play politics today.

08:45.515 --> 08:49.184
We are here because Daniel
Holden was convicted of

08:49.186 --> 08:53.522
murder and sentenced to death.

08:53.524 --> 08:57.426
We are here because of the
perverse miracle that Daniel is

08:57.428 --> 09:01.964
still alive, and because of the
outright fluke that crucial

09:01.966 --> 09:08.570
DNA evidence was not lost, or
thrown away, or destroyed.

09:08.572 --> 09:11.273
We are here because the
DNA testing conclusively

09:11.275 --> 09:14.944
disputes that there was a
sole perpetrator, or that

09:14.946 --> 09:19.515
the sole perpetrator was Daniel
Holden, as the State had claimed.

09:19.517 --> 09:22.151
Let's hope that the prosecution
and politicians go after

09:22.153 --> 09:27.723
the real killers, instead of going
after an innocent man a second time.

09:29.659 --> 09:31.059
Daniel?

09:31.061 --> 09:34.296
[ Collective cheers ]

09:34.298 --> 09:37.566
[ Applause ]

09:37.568 --> 09:41.336
Hello.

09:41.338 --> 09:47.943
I'm not sure what to make of this
drastic change of course in my life.

09:47.945 --> 09:50.279
I'm certainly not against it.

09:53.150 --> 09:58.620
Over the past two decades,
I have developed a strict

09:58.622 --> 10:05.160
routine, which I followed religiously,
you might say, a way of living

10:05.162 --> 10:09.064
and-and thinking, or not
thinking, as was often

10:09.066 --> 10:13.935
the point of, well, the point.

10:15.438 --> 10:18.774
Now, this way of being didn't
encourage the contemplation that

10:18.776 --> 10:23.078
a day like today could ever
occur, or a tomorrow like

10:23.080 --> 10:28.117
tomorrow w-will be for me now.

10:28.119 --> 10:32.054
I had convinced myself, that
kind of optimism served

10:32.056 --> 10:37.794
no useful purpose in the
world where I existed.

10:37.796 --> 10:41.130
Obviously, this radical
belief system was flawed,

10:41.132 --> 10:49.239
and was, ironically, a
kind of fantasy itself.

10:49.241 --> 10:54.578
At the least, I feel that those
specific coping skills were

10:54.580 --> 11:01.118
best suited to the
life there behind me.

11:01.120 --> 11:05.757
I doubt they will serve me so
well for the life in front of me.

11:05.759 --> 11:10.027
So, I will seriously need to
reconsider my world view.

11:18.204 --> 11:21.906
Uh, now would be a good
time to thank everyone.

11:21.908 --> 11:24.642
Yes, thank you.

11:24.644 --> 11:26.444
There are many people to thank.

11:26.446 --> 11:31.782
M-m-my mother and sister
for their enduring love,

11:31.784 --> 11:34.351
devotion, and faith.

11:36.488 --> 11:39.016
[ Music ]

12:21.199 --> 12:24.397
[ Music ]

12:29.608 --> 12:32.310
You gettin' carsick, Danny?

12:34.113 --> 12:36.381
What?

12:39.285 --> 12:43.355
I-I don't know.

12:43.357 --> 12:47.892
I feel sleepy, and
I don't know why.

12:47.894 --> 12:49.827
Go to sleep, then.

12:49.829 --> 12:52.196
Why not?

12:52.198 --> 12:54.165
I'll keep both hands
on the wheel.

12:54.167 --> 12:56.167
Hey.

12:57.402 --> 12:59.904
[ Laughing ]

13:02.041 --> 13:07.678
[ Music ]

13:30.381 --> 13:32.381
He fell asleep?

13:32.383 --> 13:36.252
Like a rock, almost the whole
way, right into the garage.

13:36.254 --> 13:37.753
So, he didn't see the town?

13:37.755 --> 13:38.821
Anything?

13:38.823 --> 13:42.425
Not even the expanded
Dollar Store.

13:44.195 --> 13:46.796
Hand me the peas, dear.

13:53.904 --> 13:55.205
Mom?

13:55.207 --> 13:56.840
Did you check the roast?

13:56.842 --> 13:58.308
I did.

13:58.310 --> 14:03.446
Mom, what happened to you
today was okay, you know?

14:03.448 --> 14:07.183
It was a long time
comin', mother.

14:07.185 --> 14:09.586
For God's sake,
it's normal, mom.

14:09.588 --> 14:11.421
How is any of this normal?

14:11.423 --> 14:12.589
How?

14:12.591 --> 14:14.624
Nothing about this has ever
been normal, Amantha,

14:14.626 --> 14:17.126
and it never will be.

14:17.128 --> 14:21.130
And I would like to just not
talk about it for a little bit.

14:21.132 --> 14:25.034
I would like to
simply make supper.

14:25.036 --> 14:27.470
Sure, mom.

14:29.406 --> 14:30.539
Hello?

14:30.541 --> 14:31.974
Anybody in here?

14:31.976 --> 14:34.543
Just us chickens!

14:34.545 --> 14:36.412
Ah, here's my buddy.

14:36.414 --> 14:37.947
Oh!

14:37.949 --> 14:40.049
Don't I get one?

14:42.252 --> 14:44.720
Don't I get one?

14:44.722 --> 14:46.889
There's one for you, too.

14:46.891 --> 14:48.992
Take what I can get.

14:55.534 --> 14:56.868
Jared: Where is he?

14:56.870 --> 14:58.670
He's in the house, right?

14:58.672 --> 15:01.406
He's upstairs taking
a bath, Jared.

15:01.408 --> 15:03.307
Oh, that's cool.

15:03.309 --> 15:05.577
Mmm-hmm-- yeah.

15:09.148 --> 15:12.482
[ Music ]

15:40.746 --> 15:44.750
[ Inmates shouting ]

15:51.991 --> 15:54.426
Guard: Knees, 4870.

16:02.369 --> 16:04.504
Up.

16:08.175 --> 16:10.577
Move it, 4870.

16:16.550 --> 16:19.085
Get up, 4870.

16:27.996 --> 16:31.699
Won't be killin' three-year-old
girls in here now, will ya?

16:32.968 --> 16:35.103
Three-year-old?

16:35.105 --> 16:37.439
Damn, voodoo.

16:37.441 --> 16:39.107
I like your style.

16:39.109 --> 16:42.477
Hope you didn't blow your
wad on the first date.

16:42.479 --> 16:43.745
Shut up!

16:43.747 --> 16:45.580
Can't take it anymore!

16:45.582 --> 16:48.783
Try and tune that out.

16:48.785 --> 16:51.119
We'll talk later.

16:51.121 --> 16:53.721
Compare notes and such.

16:59.261 --> 17:01.929
[ Humming ]

17:10.038 --> 17:13.641
[ Humming ]

17:28.656 --> 17:31.292
Dear Heavenly Father, we
thank you for this most

17:31.294 --> 17:35.762
wonderful day, for this miracle
you've bestowed upon us,

17:35.764 --> 17:39.099
for this deliverance of
Daniel back into our home.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.402
We ask for your wisdom, as
we go forward into the

17:41.404 --> 17:45.239
uncertainty of the days ahead,
that you bless this food for

17:45.241 --> 17:49.543
the nourishment of our bodies,
and forgive us of our sins.

17:49.545 --> 17:50.811
In Jesus' name, we pray.

17:50.813 --> 17:51.979
Amen.

17:51.981 --> 17:54.615
Amen.

17:54.617 --> 17:57.585
Very nice, Ted.

17:57.587 --> 17:58.919
Very nice, Ted.

17:58.921 --> 18:00.788
Thank you, Daniel.

18:00.790 --> 18:03.224
Very nice, Ted.

18:06.528 --> 18:08.829
- Well--
- Sure looks good.

18:08.831 --> 18:09.997
What do you think, buddy?

18:09.999 --> 18:11.098
Looks tasty, mom.

18:11.100 --> 18:14.802
Thank you, Jared.

18:14.804 --> 18:16.704
Can I have your plate, Danny?

18:16.706 --> 18:19.107
Sure.

18:25.882 --> 18:28.851
Danny, you gotta try
this cornbread.

18:28.853 --> 18:32.354
There's an end piece
down there somewhere.

18:32.356 --> 18:34.756
Looks great.

18:34.758 --> 18:36.058
Thank you, Jared.

18:36.060 --> 18:37.793
You're welcome.

18:37.795 --> 18:39.495
Here's some corn.

18:39.497 --> 18:41.964
Are you okay?

18:45.068 --> 18:47.468
[ Music ]

19:05.454 --> 19:07.422
I'm not checking on
you or anything.

19:07.424 --> 19:09.424
I just came outside
for a smoke.

19:12.127 --> 19:13.227
Do you wanna be left alone?

19:13.229 --> 19:15.296
I can go smoke in the backyard.

19:16.799 --> 19:18.866
I don't know.

19:18.868 --> 19:25.040
Well, you wanna do
anything later?

19:25.042 --> 19:28.042
Play hearts, or--

19:30.078 --> 19:32.012
I don't know.

19:32.014 --> 19:34.014
Go to town.

19:34.016 --> 19:35.549
Okay.

19:35.551 --> 19:39.686
See it at first when it's
not so bright, you know?

19:39.688 --> 19:42.422
Of course, honey.

19:45.192 --> 19:47.827
Five times during his
incarceration, Mr. Holden

19:47.829 --> 19:51.198
has been scheduled to die, but
each time, his execution

19:51.200 --> 19:52.666
was stayed due to appeal.

19:52.668 --> 19:54.034
Damn.

19:54.036 --> 19:57.038
[ Indistinct ]

19:57.040 --> 19:58.439
Give me another slice, babe.

19:58.441 --> 20:00.875
There is a lot to
process, right now.

20:00.877 --> 20:04.012
Uh, I'll probably
be happier later.

20:04.014 --> 20:06.481
It's almost like he's playing
for laughs, sometimes.

20:06.483 --> 20:08.016
I don't think so.

20:08.018 --> 20:10.752
He just sees
things differently.

20:10.754 --> 20:14.589
Perhaps I will be angrier
later, as I will be happier.

20:14.591 --> 20:15.557
I'm tired of watching this.

20:15.559 --> 20:16.825
See what else is on.

20:16.827 --> 20:18.827
No, don't!

20:18.829 --> 20:20.728
Damn, I was just kidding.

20:20.730 --> 20:22.830
How does it feel to be outside?

20:22.832 --> 20:23.665
Free.

20:23.667 --> 20:27.635
What'd you think when you
first saw your family?

20:27.637 --> 20:31.339
Thought of family, uh, "we."

20:31.341 --> 20:34.842
Where'd they go?

20:34.844 --> 20:37.745
Just ridin' around.

20:37.747 --> 20:40.581
I feel he should have
his room back, mom.

20:40.583 --> 20:42.683
No, Jared.
That's your room now.

20:42.685 --> 20:46.053
Yeah, but it's not like
he went off to college.

20:46.055 --> 20:48.856
Jared, Daniel wanted
you to have his room.

20:48.858 --> 20:50.157
He told you that?

20:50.159 --> 20:52.626
Yes, a long time ago.

20:52.628 --> 20:56.630
It made him very happy to
know you were in there.

20:56.632 --> 20:58.999
He didn't hardly say
anything tonight.

20:59.001 --> 21:02.435
Well, he doesn't
know how to, honey.

21:02.437 --> 21:04.504
I kinda don't, either.

21:04.506 --> 21:06.573
Nobody does.

21:06.575 --> 21:09.509
We'll just all learn together.

21:09.511 --> 21:12.045
Okay?

21:13.748 --> 21:17.250
This way of being didn't encourage
the contemplation that a day

21:17.252 --> 21:20.454
like today could ever occur.

21:20.456 --> 21:22.456
Look at him.

21:22.458 --> 21:25.292
You tell me he didn't
kill that girl.

21:25.294 --> 21:26.393
He killed her.

21:26.395 --> 21:29.463
Yeah, but there's a little bit
of a hole in the case, now.

21:29.465 --> 21:31.833
They've got multiple semen
samples, and the only sample

21:31.835 --> 21:34.335
they can single out
was not Holden.

21:34.337 --> 21:36.137
Son of a bitch confessed, CJ.

21:36.139 --> 21:37.271
Remember?

21:37.273 --> 21:38.505
Yeah, I remember.

21:38.507 --> 21:40.374
Then why in the hell would a
person confess to somethin'

21:40.376 --> 21:41.642
they didn't do?

21:41.644 --> 21:44.345
You've had 19 years to
think on that, and you

21:44.347 --> 21:47.581
ain't figured out an answer
other than he did it?

21:47.583 --> 21:49.383
Meaning what?

21:49.385 --> 21:53.721
One of those boys saw Holden on top
of that girl, forcin' himself.

21:53.723 --> 21:57.124
But, without a definite hit on
his sperm, those witnesses

21:57.126 --> 22:00.461
ain't gonna be quite as
solid this time, are they?

22:00.463 --> 22:02.163
And they might
even be suspects.

22:02.165 --> 22:06.167
We know that, CJ, and nobody's
decidin' anything, right now.

22:06.169 --> 22:07.435
Decidin' what?

22:07.437 --> 22:09.670
Don't the DA
have a say in this?

22:09.672 --> 22:11.438
She's gonna be brought in.

22:11.440 --> 22:14.041
But, not tonight?

22:14.043 --> 22:17.244
No.

22:17.246 --> 22:20.380
Look, it's reasonable to think
a couple of them other boys

22:20.382 --> 22:23.183
coulda had intercourse with her.

22:23.185 --> 22:24.951
Doesn't mean they killed her.

22:24.953 --> 22:27.554
Doesn't mean they didn't.

22:33.327 --> 22:36.229
Is this, like, weird?

22:37.898 --> 22:40.433
It's not unweird.

22:40.435 --> 22:44.037
How long has that video
store been there?

22:44.039 --> 22:48.008
Was there about 15 years.

22:48.010 --> 22:49.877
Was?

22:49.879 --> 22:52.880
Shut down about a year ago.

22:56.452 --> 23:01.422
Hey, we can go to the
Target in Mansfield.

23:01.424 --> 23:03.224
What's the Target?

23:03.226 --> 23:05.760
You are.

23:07.596 --> 23:09.097
I'm sorry.

23:09.099 --> 23:10.732
I'm sorry.

23:10.734 --> 23:11.766
I-I don't know why I said that.

23:11.768 --> 23:15.336
It just came out.

23:15.338 --> 23:17.939
You're a funny, sister.

23:17.941 --> 23:19.340
Oh, good.

23:19.342 --> 23:21.076
You got it.

23:21.078 --> 23:24.179
[ Chuckling ]

23:24.181 --> 23:25.681
That's kinda how I deal.

23:25.683 --> 23:26.982
God loves humor.

23:26.984 --> 23:28.517
Exactly.

23:28.519 --> 23:31.587
Of course, you would know
about that, wouldn't you?

23:32.889 --> 23:34.790
I mean, God!

23:34.792 --> 23:36.492
I did it, again.

23:36.494 --> 23:38.628
Mmm-hmm.

23:38.630 --> 23:46.135
We call it lethal injection humor--
more humane, but not as funny.

23:49.872 --> 23:51.273
She was his girlfriend.

23:51.275 --> 23:53.508
Gives him even more motive.
Can you not see that?

23:53.510 --> 23:55.410
Carl.

23:59.581 --> 24:04.251
Nobody wants to open this
back up, CJ, all the pain.

24:04.253 --> 24:07.922
But, that's no reason
to let a killer walk.

24:07.924 --> 24:11.492
I've got doubts he
is the killer, now.

24:11.494 --> 24:16.464
But, are they reasonable doubts?

24:23.204 --> 24:26.641
Just forget about the
confession for a minute.

24:26.643 --> 24:30.645
He was found sitting beside the
girl's corpse, just holding

24:30.647 --> 24:35.182
her hand, speaking gibberish
half the time, and the other

24:35.184 --> 24:38.619
half saying how sorry he was.

24:41.156 --> 24:43.658
He didn't go get help.

24:43.660 --> 24:46.627
He didn't scream out.

24:46.629 --> 24:51.600
He spent the morning gathering
wildflowers to put in her hair, CJ.

24:51.602 --> 24:55.070
And I was the one who found
him with her, remember?

24:55.072 --> 24:57.606
I remember.

25:00.010 --> 25:03.045
I just wanna make
sure you remember.

25:03.047 --> 25:05.114
Well, what do you
want from me, Roland?

25:05.116 --> 25:06.949
Just tell me.

25:06.951 --> 25:11.487
CJ, we just wanna know, if Holden's
re-indicted by the new DA--

25:11.489 --> 25:14.356
I'm retired, remember?

25:14.358 --> 25:19.161
You might have to testify, at
some point, grand jury and all.

25:19.163 --> 25:21.630
No shit.

25:21.632 --> 25:23.131
Mistakes were made, CJ.

25:23.133 --> 25:25.667
No doubt about it.

25:25.669 --> 25:30.104
We've all made mistakes in
our own individual lives,

25:30.106 --> 25:34.876
things we regret, do different.

25:34.878 --> 25:37.579
That's beside the point,
whether Holden is the killer,

25:37.581 --> 25:42.150
which I believe, deep
in my heart he is.

25:42.152 --> 25:47.521
I couldn't have lived with myself all
these years otherwise, could you?

25:47.523 --> 25:49.957
And I'll be damned if I'm gonna
let him get away with it now,

25:49.959 --> 25:53.895
just because we tried to protect
an innocent girl's reputation,

25:53.897 --> 25:57.799
and so as to spare her
mother even more pain.

26:00.235 --> 26:02.604
I'll review the case.

26:08.344 --> 26:12.648
Try and get everything
straight in my mind, again.

26:15.986 --> 26:19.021
Where's Holden at anyway?

26:19.023 --> 26:21.424
At his mama's.

26:21.426 --> 26:24.661
He's not movin'
back here, is he?

26:24.663 --> 26:26.296
Don't know.

26:26.298 --> 26:29.566
Lord-lord-lord.

26:29.568 --> 26:32.702
No matter how you slice
it, I sometimes wonder

26:32.704 --> 26:36.273
if this is ever goin' away.

26:36.275 --> 26:38.375
Hmm?

26:49.301 --> 26:52.103
[ Cell phone vibrating ]

26:52.105 --> 26:53.304
Hello.

26:53.306 --> 26:54.939
Hey, it's after 12.

26:54.941 --> 26:56.074
I know.

26:56.076 --> 26:57.442
What are ya'll doin'?

26:57.444 --> 26:59.977
Just-just drivin' around.

26:59.979 --> 27:01.679
Why are you whispering?

27:01.681 --> 27:03.815
Daniel's asleep.

27:03.817 --> 27:07.818
Well, are you gonna
drive around all night?

27:07.820 --> 27:09.486
Probably not.

27:09.488 --> 27:11.055
I'm not gonna worry, then.

27:11.057 --> 27:13.991
No, go on to sleep.

27:22.467 --> 27:25.703
I'm not breakin'
the law, asshole.

27:26.972 --> 27:29.480
[ Music ]

27:44.190 --> 27:46.291
What, are we in high school?

27:46.293 --> 27:48.927
Are you kiddin' me?

27:59.305 --> 28:01.566
[ Music ]

28:57.432 --> 28:59.933
You like?

28:59.935 --> 29:02.903
It's, um--

29:05.340 --> 29:10.244
I just wanted it to be
special for ya, honey.

29:10.246 --> 29:13.614
I would say you succeeded.

29:16.718 --> 29:21.188
Thank you, Amantha,
for everything.

29:21.190 --> 29:24.492
You're quite welcome, brother.

29:24.494 --> 29:26.594
Anytime.

29:34.469 --> 29:36.070
We're lost, aren't we?

29:36.072 --> 29:38.272
Totally.

29:43.110 --> 29:44.144
Sorry I'm late.

29:44.146 --> 29:45.178
Mmm-hmm.

29:45.180 --> 29:46.245
Couldn't sleep last night.

29:46.247 --> 29:47.480
I was wound up like a top.

29:47.482 --> 29:49.148
Yep.

29:49.150 --> 29:53.352
Me and Tawney got
in a big fight.

29:53.354 --> 29:55.221
You see all that coverage?

29:55.223 --> 29:58.057
Some of it.

29:58.059 --> 29:59.359
Boy, it's controversial, huh?

29:59.361 --> 30:01.594
It's that.

30:05.933 --> 30:08.000
So, when is he gonna
start workin' here?

30:08.002 --> 30:10.469
Whenever he wants to.

30:13.139 --> 30:16.842
Dad, the minute he steps foot in
this store, at least half the people

30:16.844 --> 30:19.277
who do business here
are gonna stop coming.

30:19.279 --> 30:21.647
I'm aware of that.

30:21.649 --> 30:25.617
A 50% cut in revenue is not
gonna support two households.

30:25.619 --> 30:26.985
I'm aware of that, too.

30:26.987 --> 30:31.890
- Look, maybe if we explained
the situation-- - No, sir.

30:31.892 --> 30:33.958
Dad, he deserves to have all
the information to make

30:33.960 --> 30:34.826
an informed decision.

30:34.828 --> 30:36.895
Absolutely not, Teddy.

30:36.897 --> 30:38.697
Now, listen to me.

30:38.699 --> 30:40.699
This is his family business.

30:40.701 --> 30:41.700
It's not ours.

30:41.702 --> 30:43.034
We just married into it.

30:43.036 --> 30:46.404
Now, if he wants to come
work here, it's his right.

30:46.406 --> 30:50.208
We can't put that kind of weight
on him, not with everything else

30:50.210 --> 30:53.844
he's had to deal
with in his life.

30:53.846 --> 30:58.015
Well, I might as well start
lookin' for a new job, right now.

31:13.932 --> 31:16.367
"Of Human Bondage".

31:16.369 --> 31:18.135
"Of Human Bondage"?

31:18.137 --> 31:22.306
You want me to read a book
called "Of Human Bondage"?

31:22.308 --> 31:24.675
It's not that kind of bondage.

31:24.677 --> 31:26.811
I would hope so.

31:27.679 --> 31:30.448
Hey, will I be glad when you get
past your dead white man writin'

31:30.450 --> 31:33.451
about white Europe stage.

31:33.453 --> 31:35.820
I am on kind of a jag.

31:35.822 --> 31:38.323
You oughta sprinkle in a
little "Arthur Arthur!"

31:38.325 --> 31:40.558
Brother-brother
from time to time.

31:40.560 --> 31:41.893
Okay, sure.

31:41.895 --> 31:44.061
I got somethin' I think
you'll appreciate, too.

31:44.063 --> 31:45.830
It ain't modern times, either.

31:45.832 --> 31:50.101
It's about black folks owning slaves
in the South before the Civil War.

31:50.103 --> 31:51.069
Curious.

31:51.071 --> 31:55.339
Free men buyin' their
brothers and sisters for--

31:55.341 --> 31:56.641
Hey, man, just read the book.

31:56.643 --> 31:58.142
I'm hooked already.

31:58.144 --> 32:01.480
Then, I'll give your dead Somerset
Maugham a shot when you're done.

32:01.482 --> 32:04.283
But, if it don't grab me
early, I'm settin' it down.

32:04.285 --> 32:07.452
No rules for a club
that's not a club.

32:19.266 --> 32:25.837
My lawyer said he'd be more
optimistic about an appeal

32:25.839 --> 32:29.641
if I hadn't done it.

32:29.643 --> 32:31.943
How did you respond?

32:31.945 --> 32:34.412
Just nodded, you know?

32:34.414 --> 32:37.015
Less money they get paid, the
more sensitive they are.

32:37.017 --> 32:41.553
So, well, hell, at least this
one comes by for a visit

32:41.555 --> 32:45.124
every once in a while.

32:45.126 --> 32:47.492
I don't know.

32:47.494 --> 32:51.697
Maybe I oughta just
throw in the towel.

32:51.699 --> 32:54.099
Shorten the exit.

32:54.101 --> 32:56.902
I can't do time the
way you do it.

32:56.904 --> 32:58.303
I don't do time.

32:58.305 --> 33:00.238
That's what I'm talkin' about.

33:00.240 --> 33:03.141
I can't do time by not doin'
time the way you do time.

33:03.143 --> 33:05.643
All that cross-legged
shit just make me antsy.

33:05.645 --> 33:08.012
Well, maybe if you didn't
judge the experience while

33:08.014 --> 33:11.783
- it was happenin', then you--
- Man, shut up!

33:15.822 --> 33:18.123
You know what's whack?

33:22.128 --> 33:24.496
Lots of things.

33:24.498 --> 33:29.301
Sittin' in this tomb, day after
day, puttin' up with this food,

33:29.303 --> 33:32.538
puttin' up wit' your
pale, white ass.

33:32.540 --> 33:41.148
What's whack is... I still
wanna live, every day.

33:41.150 --> 33:44.652
What's that about?

33:44.654 --> 33:46.887
Vitamin A deficiency.

33:46.889 --> 33:50.157
[ Laughing ]

33:54.797 --> 33:59.534
You trip me out, D.

33:59.536 --> 34:02.804
You trip me out, Kerwin.

34:10.980 --> 34:15.016
Hungry?

34:15.018 --> 34:17.518
I think I'd like a beer.

34:17.521 --> 34:21.157
Oh, um, let's see.

34:21.159 --> 34:23.726
Teddy usually has one
or two in the fridge.

34:23.728 --> 34:26.128
Sometimes, he stops
by for a visit.

34:26.130 --> 34:27.263
Here we go.

34:27.264 --> 34:28.264
Would he mind?

34:28.266 --> 34:29.831
Of course not.

34:29.833 --> 34:32.034
Yeah.

34:38.475 --> 34:40.710
I'm payin' bills.

34:42.646 --> 34:45.281
Sit down, if you'd like.

34:50.054 --> 34:55.993
Uh, I don't think I wanna
become computer literate...

34:55.995 --> 34:59.030
or mobile phone
literate, either.

34:59.032 --> 35:02.600
Might be a little
much, all at once.

35:15.681 --> 35:20.385
I-I would like a television,
though, with a movie player,

35:20.387 --> 35:23.755
a-a DVD player.

35:23.757 --> 35:25.156
We can do that.

35:25.158 --> 35:27.291
I'll pay you back, as
soon as I start work.

35:27.293 --> 35:29.560
Don't be silly.

35:29.562 --> 35:30.728
Okay.

35:30.730 --> 35:35.900
No, I mean, we already
have one of those.

35:35.902 --> 35:38.002
I see.

35:50.882 --> 35:54.418
Thank you for the books, mother.

35:54.420 --> 35:58.456
Of course.

35:58.458 --> 36:01.892
You know, I-I won't be
around here forever, mother.

36:01.894 --> 36:03.828
What do you mean?

36:03.830 --> 36:05.896
Well, at your house and Ted's.

36:05.898 --> 36:10.534
This is your house, too, Daniel--
you can stay as long as you like.

36:10.536 --> 36:15.439
Well, I can't quite get a handle
on the concept of time yet.

36:15.441 --> 36:18.342
There have been moments here
today where I feel like

36:18.344 --> 36:26.751
I've only been gone a few weeks,
and I'm still in high school.

36:26.753 --> 36:31.322
But mostly, it seems
like I was always there.

36:35.093 --> 36:38.295
So, you may have to
tell me, mother.

36:38.297 --> 36:40.630
Tell you?

36:40.632 --> 36:44.799
When it's time for me to leave.

36:52.174 --> 36:53.074
Hey, Jimmy.

36:53.076 --> 36:53.841
How ya doin'?

36:53.843 --> 36:54.509
Good.

36:54.511 --> 36:55.910
- Hi, Senator.
- Good morning.

36:55.912 --> 36:57.078
How are ya, sir?

36:57.080 --> 36:58.779
Saw your speech, Senator.

36:58.781 --> 37:00.314
But, I still don't understand
why they let him out,

37:00.316 --> 37:01.248
if he said he did it.

37:01.250 --> 37:02.983
Oh, I'm as baffled
as you are, Lonny.

37:02.985 --> 37:06.519
My advice is, let your feelings be
known to our current prosecutor.

37:06.521 --> 37:10.756
A little heat might
get things cookin'.

37:10.758 --> 37:14.392
Sheriff.

37:14.394 --> 37:15.593
Where's your daddy?

37:15.595 --> 37:17.227
He's got belly problems.

37:17.229 --> 37:19.496
Who ain't?

37:19.498 --> 37:21.898
Ain't you a sight for
sore eyes, Marcy?

37:21.900 --> 37:23.433
What'll you have, sweetie?

37:23.435 --> 37:26.469
Everybody calls me Senator,
and you call me, "sweetie."

37:26.471 --> 37:28.604
Well, that's 'cause I've known
you "sweetie" a lot longer

37:28.606 --> 37:29.838
than I've known you "Senator."

37:29.840 --> 37:31.606
That's a fact.

37:31.608 --> 37:36.642
I'll have a wildcat
breakfast, extra sausage.

37:36.644 --> 37:41.313
Okay, you got it,
Senator-- sweetie.

37:41.315 --> 37:43.414
You ain't still
tappin' that, are ya?

37:43.416 --> 37:45.783
No, I'm on the wagon.

37:45.785 --> 37:47.685
Oh, extra biscuits, Marcy!

37:47.687 --> 37:49.619
Thought you were havin'
belly problems, too.

37:49.621 --> 37:51.054
Perception, Sheriff.

37:51.056 --> 37:54.057
I'm gonna eat like a man
without a worry in the world.

37:56.594 --> 37:59.862
Have you seen today's
"Atlanta Journal?"

37:59.864 --> 38:02.297
Two hours ago.

38:02.299 --> 38:03.832
Your feelings hurt?

38:03.834 --> 38:05.900
I'm tinkled pink.

38:05.902 --> 38:07.735
Having the big city papers
attacking me down here

38:07.737 --> 38:11.372
is a asset, not a liability.

38:16.277 --> 38:20.280
You get a chance to speak
to those witnesses yet?

38:20.282 --> 38:24.484
Wasn't sure if I should.

38:24.486 --> 38:29.388
She'll wanna talk to
'em, madame prosecutor.

38:29.390 --> 38:31.324
I'd imagine.

38:34.895 --> 38:37.597
This is as messed up
as a pile of hangers.

39:12.299 --> 39:16.402
Trey: A funny place
to have a reunion.

39:16.404 --> 39:19.605
Georgie: Not so funny.

39:19.607 --> 39:22.708
How's Florida?

39:22.710 --> 39:24.844
I don't care for it.

39:28.315 --> 39:29.915
Where's your car, Georgie?

39:29.917 --> 39:31.750
I took the bus.

39:31.752 --> 39:34.986
Make sure I wasn't
being followed.

39:34.988 --> 39:36.555
By who?

39:39.325 --> 39:41.626
Now they know what
they didn't know.

39:41.628 --> 39:44.462
Yes, kinda big news around here.

39:48.267 --> 39:50.902
Did you kill her, Trey?

39:50.904 --> 39:53.204
What?

39:53.206 --> 39:56.107
No.

39:56.109 --> 39:59.377
Did you, Georgie?

39:59.379 --> 40:00.879
No.

40:04.917 --> 40:07.352
He killed her.

40:07.354 --> 40:09.454
How do you know?

40:09.456 --> 40:12.324
It's the only thing
that makes sense to me.

40:15.461 --> 40:16.861
I think about it a lot.

40:16.863 --> 40:19.397
That's always been your problem.

40:19.399 --> 40:22.133
We were just kids.

40:22.135 --> 40:26.438
Wasn't real, you know?

40:31.911 --> 40:34.546
What are you gonna do, Trey?

40:34.548 --> 40:36.881
Tell the truth.

40:36.883 --> 40:38.984
What is the truth?

40:40.653 --> 40:43.516
[ Music ]

41:03.444 --> 41:04.677
Well, what's your point, Jon?

41:04.679 --> 41:06.479
My point is that there
are 100 different ways

41:06.481 --> 41:09.349
the prosecution can convince a
jury that Daniel did this,

41:09.351 --> 41:11.817
no matter what the DNA
does or doesn't say.

41:11.819 --> 41:12.785
Of course, they can.

41:12.787 --> 41:14.686
That's what they do.

41:14.688 --> 41:16.755
They're in the convincing
business, Jon.

41:16.757 --> 41:19.324
First, they
convince themselves.

41:19.326 --> 41:21.960
Then, they convince anybody
necessary, by any means

41:21.962 --> 41:25.497
necessary, including sometimes
the defendants themselves.

41:25.499 --> 41:28.000
All you have to do, if it
comes down to it, is to

41:28.002 --> 41:30.402
convince one out of twelve
people in a jury that the

41:30.404 --> 41:34.706
prosecutors are lying, cheating,
son of a bitch bastards!

41:38.477 --> 41:41.446
[ Sighing ]

41:41.448 --> 41:43.682
I'm sorry.

41:43.684 --> 41:47.352
Understandable.

41:47.354 --> 41:49.421
How is Daniel doing, anyway?

41:49.423 --> 41:51.056
I don't know.

41:51.058 --> 41:54.459
I just wanna hug him all the time,
but I know it'd freak him out.

41:54.461 --> 41:58.096
Maybe you can sneak
one in, occasionally.

41:58.098 --> 42:01.466
Why couldn't Ted, Jr. be

41:58.899 --> 42:01.466
wrongly convicted and spend more
than half his life on death row?

42:01.468 --> 42:03.534
He'd probably come out fine.

42:03.536 --> 42:05.203
That might be a little harsh.

42:05.205 --> 42:07.138
No, it's not.

42:07.140 --> 42:09.274
I can't imagine you
and Ted, Jr. living in

42:09.276 --> 42:11.009
the same house as adolescents.

42:11.011 --> 42:14.245
We had to share a bathroom,
too-- beyond gross.

42:14.247 --> 42:15.079
Ew.

42:15.081 --> 42:16.381
It's not funny.

42:16.383 --> 42:18.115
No, of course not.

42:18.117 --> 42:20.451
I need therapy just for
those three years alone.

42:20.453 --> 42:22.086
Post Traumatic Ted Syndrome.

42:22.088 --> 42:27.625
It's so under reported, too.

42:27.627 --> 42:29.327
I'm coming down tomorrow.

42:29.329 --> 42:32.630
Okay, but why so soon?

42:32.632 --> 42:37.702
Rutherford Gaines has
pancreatic cancer.

42:37.704 --> 42:38.869
Really?

42:38.871 --> 42:41.472
I don't wanna regret not
asking him anything important.

42:41.474 --> 42:43.107
The only thing I regret is
that he was Daniel's lawyer

42:43.109 --> 42:45.342
in the first place.

42:45.344 --> 42:46.877
Talk about a pussy.

42:46.879 --> 42:48.946
Well, I think he
regrets that now, too.

42:48.948 --> 42:53.450
Old man regrets-- hollow
and too frickin' late.

42:53.452 --> 42:55.485
But, I'm glad you're
comin' down, Jon.

42:55.487 --> 42:57.921
Me, too, Amantha.

42:57.923 --> 43:01.124
I'm real glad
you're on our side.

43:07.365 --> 43:09.200
[ Knocking ]

43:20.780 --> 43:21.913
Hello.

43:21.915 --> 43:23.482
This has a DVD player in it.

43:23.484 --> 43:26.185
You can watch movies and stuff.

43:26.187 --> 43:27.586
Is it yours?

43:27.588 --> 43:30.956
Yeah, but I've got an iPad,
so I stream, mostly.

43:30.958 --> 43:32.691
Okay.

43:32.693 --> 43:34.293
Well, thank you, Jared.

43:34.295 --> 43:35.961
Yeah.

43:39.131 --> 43:41.700
Uh, I could help you hook it up.

43:41.702 --> 43:45.937
I mean, I know you just plug it
in, but I know where the plug is.

43:45.939 --> 43:47.873
I think I need help.

44:03.224 --> 44:06.025
I'm guessing you don't
have any DVD's yet.

44:06.027 --> 44:07.393
No.

44:07.395 --> 44:12.531
Yeah, I didn't think so, but
I didn't want to, you know.

44:12.533 --> 44:13.766
Presume?

44:13.768 --> 44:16.201
Y-yeah, exactly, presume.

44:16.203 --> 44:19.104
Uh, anyways, I've got
kind of a collection.

44:19.106 --> 44:21.039
I've been thinking, like,
if you haven't seen movies

44:21.041 --> 44:23.809
in a long time, which ones
would be good to start with

44:23.811 --> 44:25.577
and work your way up.

44:25.579 --> 44:27.646
I'd appreciate the guidance.

44:27.648 --> 44:28.680
Okay.

44:28.682 --> 44:29.848
Well, you can go a lot of ways.

44:29.850 --> 44:33.685
But, uh, one of my favorites--
it's called "Dazed And Confused."

44:33.687 --> 44:35.921
I like the title.

44:35.923 --> 44:38.490
Yeah, I heard that.

44:38.492 --> 44:40.592
Uh, anyway, it's a cool movie.

44:40.594 --> 44:42.828
Not too heavy or
anything like that.

44:42.830 --> 44:46.565
And, um, I could even
watch it with you.

44:46.567 --> 44:49.902
Or-or, you might wanna
be by yourself.

44:49.904 --> 44:51.804
I mean, it's all good.

44:51.806 --> 44:57.009
I think I'd rather
watch it with you.

44:57.011 --> 44:59.644
Oh, sure-- cool.

45:01.681 --> 45:03.882
Uh, right now?

45:03.884 --> 45:05.717
Oh, did you mean right now?

45:05.719 --> 45:07.185
Uh, yeah, yeah, sure.

45:07.187 --> 45:09.388
I-I'll go get it.

45:12.259 --> 45:16.788
